'''pyroclastic flow'''

#A flow of [[volcanic]] ash, dust, [[rock]]s and debris that cascades down the slope of a [[volcano]] during an [[eruption]]. Pyroclastic flows are very dangerous, reaching speeds greater than 60 miles per hour and temperatures in excess of 800 degrees Farenheit.

